<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870828-0101 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Neiman-Marcus GetsIts New Top OfficersFrom General Cinema</HL><DD> 08/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS GCN </IN><DATELINE> CHESTNUT HILL, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Neiman-Marcus Group Inc. announced its new officers and named nine directors following completion of the restructuring of Carter Hawley Hale Stores Inc., Los Angeles, which previously owned the specialty-store chain.    Neiman-Marcus is 60%-owned by General Cinema Corp., a soft drink and movie theater company. Four General Cinema officers will be Neiman-Marcus directors and will hold operating posts identical to their General Cinema jobs.    They are: Richard A. Smith, chairman and chief executive officer; J. Atwood Ives, vice chairman and chief financial officer; Robert J. Tarr Jr., president and chief operating officer, and Samuel Frankenheim, senior vice president and general counsel.    Three Neiman-Marcus directors served on the Carter Hawley board. They are John T. Dorrance Jr., chairman of the executive committee of Campbell Soup Co.; Walter J. Salmon, professor of retailing at Harvard Business School; and Jean Head Sisco, a management consultant.    Also named to the board were Gary L. Countryman, chief executive of Liberty Mutual Insurance Co., and Francis C. Rooney, chairman of the executive committee of Melville Corp. </TEXT></DOC>